The course gives theoretical and practical knowledge of different therapeutic modalities and their application in physiotherapy.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the different therapeutic modalities along with principles and possibilities of using them in physiotherapy of various conditions and injuries.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - Knows the indications and contraindications for the use of different therapeutic modalities in physical therapy and the safety precautions of applying them on various patients - Can choose the most appropriate therapy modalities to reduce pain and modulate the musculoskeletal function and promote tissue healing - Knows the principles of electrophysiological evaluation of nerves and muscles. - Can select and safely apply the appropriate therapeutic modalities for patients/clients with various conditions and injuries.
